ce:section.ce:para:
Wheat straw was selected as the representative lignocellulose from Hubei province (China). The straw was rinsed repeatedly and then desiccated in a drying cabinet at 60 °C for 72 h. We used all kinds of chemical reagents in the analytical grade or best available grade (
                        Supporting information S1.1
                     ). A typically hydrothermal treatment was carried out to prepare GCQDs in an autoclave (
                        Supporting information S1.2
                     ). The confinement growth of Co-MOFs was conducted within the pretreated wheat straw to fabricate multifunctional Co-N-C materials (
                        Supporting information S1.3
                     ). The morphology, microstructure, elemental analysis, surface chemical states, and specific surface area of GCQDs and Co-N-C were performed to evaluate their performances of multifunctional water purification, including metal-ion sensing, catalytic antibiotic dissociation, and capacitive deionization (
                        Supporting information S1.4
                     ).
